11:17.051 --> 11:17.885
- Yeah?

11:19.387 --> 11:20.763
- Yeah, I really            
        liked that article

11:20.763 --> 11:22.598
you did on art               
       therapy for veterans.

11:24.433 --> 11:26.686
- Oh yeah, I did that in school.

11:26.686 --> 11:27.520
- Yeah?

11:28.604 --> 11:30.356
My daddy was a vet.

11:30.356 --> 11:32.066
He would have liked it.

11:32.066 --> 11:33.609
- I'm honored.

11:33.609 --> 11:35.277
Yeah, I wish I did           
       more stuff like that.

11:35.277 --> 11:37.071
- Well, man, now             
       here's your chance.

11:37.071 --> 11:38.572
We got a hell of a story here.

11:39.699 --> 11:41.075
I'm glad you're on it with me.

11:43.577 --> 11:45.204
Here.

11:45.204 --> 11:47.415
(can pops)

11:49.250 --> 11:52.962
Dear Lord Jesus, we pray        
    that we be straightforward

11:52.962 --> 11:54.463
like the sky-reaching tree,

11:55.881 --> 11:58.884
that our souls be clear       
      like spring water,

11:58.884 --> 12:01.595
and that you be our constant     
   companion on this trip,

12:02.972 --> 12:04.640
and that the squatches       
       be ever plentiful.

12:05.766 --> 12:07.101
Amen.

12:07.101 --> 12:07.935
- Amen.

12:09.437 --> 12:10.271
- Woo!

12:11.480 --> 12:12.898
(uptempo folk music)

12:12.898 --> 12:14.275
All right, buddy, let's go!

12:16.402 --> 12:20.990
Ready to sail into the wind

12:20.990 --> 12:25.953
Heading west to           
        find my reason

12:25.953 --> 12:30.291
Longing for something       
      greater than this

12:30.291 --> 12:32.418
And I'm ripe with

12:32.418 --> 12:34.253
- [Josh] So what got you         
   into all this stuff anyway?

12:34.253 --> 12:36.005
- Squatching?            
           - Yeah.

12:36.005 --> 12:37.798
- Oh, my pawpaw.

12:37.798 --> 12:39.258
He and I used to be obsessed     
   with this documentary

12:39.258 --> 12:40.926
called "The Bigfoot Tape."

12:40.926 --> 12:42.595
Used to take me               
      squatching all the time,

12:42.595 --> 12:45.139
which was really just        
       fun camping trips.

12:45.139 --> 12:47.099
It was a way of escaping.

12:47.099 --> 12:49.310
You know, home life was rough.

12:49.310 --> 12:52.146
Well, that Bigfoot tape       
      turned out to be a hoax.

12:52.146 --> 12:53.647
- You know, a lot of people      
   watching are gonna think

12:53.647 --> 12:55.316
what you're doing is a hoax.

12:55.316 --> 12:57.193
- But see, I got proof.

12:57.193 --> 12:58.986
- So many years, you think      
    we'd already have proof.

12:58.986 --> 13:01.489
I mean, where's             
        all the evidence?

13:01.489 --> 13:04.325
We don't even know where      
      Bigfoot lives or sleeps.

13:04.325 --> 13:05.367
- You really asking?

13:07.161 --> 13:10.831
Bigfoot sleeps in burrows,       
   kind of like big holes, dens.

13:10.831 --> 13:14.627
I've never seen one myself,      
   but much like God himself,

13:14.627 --> 13:17.713
just 'cause you don't see him,   
   don't mean he ain't there.

13:17.713 --> 13:19.340
- I'm a journalist.

13:19.340 --> 13:21.175
I can't believe it          
        without seeing it.

13:22.635 --> 13:24.178
- Well, I guess hell's       
       full of journalists.

13:25.137 --> 13:28.641
- (laughs) Touche, Red.

13:28.641 --> 13:29.475
Touche.

13:31.352 --> 13:35.856
I'm on the move

13:35.856 --> 13:40.820
Out into the              
        great, wide open

13:40.820 --> 13:45.032
Look out world, here I come

13:45.032 --> 13:49.537
Hoist up my sails          
       and ride the wind

13:52.998 --> 13:54.375
- Whoa.

13:54.375 --> 13:56.043
What's, what's that for?

13:57.419 --> 13:59.547
- Shooting bait, scaring      
      bears, protection.

13:59.547 --> 14:01.048
You want one?

14:01.048 --> 14:02.925
- No, I'm not really          
      comfortable around guns.

14:04.051 --> 14:05.594
- To be honest, we're a little

14:05.594 --> 14:06.887
too comfortable with         
       guns around here.

14:06.887 --> 14:08.264
Don't tell Kyle I said that.

14:09.515 --> 14:10.891
(truck door bangs)

14:10.891 --> 14:11.934
All right, let's go.

14:16.063 --> 14:18.941
(leaves crunching)

14:20.693 --> 14:23.529
(distant banging)

14:25.239 --> 14:28.033
(stick clapping)

14:33.205 --> 14:35.249
(distant banging)

14:35.249 --> 14:37.626
Did you catch that on tape?

14:37.626 --> 14:39.378
- Nah, I missed it.

14:40.796 --> 14:42.214
- Then you missed           
        something rare.

14:43.632 --> 14:44.967
They're hardly out          
        during the day.

14:44.967 --> 14:46.260
- That was Bigfoot?

14:46.260 --> 14:48.137
- Sure was.

14:48.137 --> 14:50.389
They use knocks to communicate   
   their location to each other.

14:53.058 --> 14:55.436
- You sure it wasn't a squirrel   
 telling a knock, knock joke?

15:00.649 --> 15:01.483
- Good one.

15:08.574 --> 15:11.076
(tense music)

15:12.953 --> 15:14.496
Welcome to the               
       only Sasquatch trap

15:14.496 --> 15:16.123
south of the Mason-Dixon line.

15:20.669 --> 15:22.671
I brought a bunch of         
       bait up this morning.

15:27.259 --> 15:29.345
- I always thought              
    Bigfoot lived in the PNW.

15:29.345 --> 15:31.972
- You keep talking           
       like there's only one.

15:31.972 --> 15:33.265
It's a whole species.

15:33.265 --> 15:35.351
Australia, they got Yowies.

15:35.351 --> 15:36.977
Nepal, they got Yetis.

15:36.977 --> 15:38.812
And here, we got Sasquatch.

15:38.812 --> 15:41.148
(tense music continues)

15:41.148 --> 15:43.817
(Josh chuckles)

15:45.486 --> 15:47.321
This here's a trip wire.

15:47.321 --> 15:48.989
That way when she comes       
      to get the bait...

15:48.989 --> 15:51.325
(bars slam)

15:53.869 --> 15:55.663
She keeps eating            
        bait out of here,

15:55.663 --> 15:58.165
but I only had the trip       
      wire put in last week.

15:59.333 --> 16:01.210
- How do you know it was her?

16:01.210 --> 16:02.336
(tongue clicking)

16:02.336 --> 16:03.170
- Check it out.

16:06.715 --> 16:07.841
It's pretty cool, huh?

16:10.177 --> 16:12.012
(tool clicks)

16:12.012 --> 16:14.515
(bars scrape)

16:15.683 --> 16:18.519
(flame crackling)

16:20.354 --> 16:21.480
- Wow, that's...

16:22.564 --> 16:24.525
- [Red] It's convincing.

16:24.525 --> 16:26.735
I don't know why you need       
    any more proof than that.

16:31.156 --> 16:33.367
- Thanks for setting         
       up the tents.

16:33.367 --> 16:34.368
- Oh man, no sweat.

16:34.368 --> 16:36.203
(can pops)

16:36.203 --> 16:38.580
You know, I figure we got        
   about two days to catch her.

16:42.167 --> 16:43.085
- What if we don't?

16:44.545 --> 16:45.879
- Well, then you'll          
       bully me like you did

16:45.879 --> 16:47.089
that Flat Earth Lady.

16:49.925 --> 16:51.760
- All right, about          
        that video so--

16:51.760 --> 16:54.054
- Hey man, look, I know          
   you wouldn't do that to me.

16:56.223 --> 16:58.058
I told you I googled you.

17:02.062 --> 17:05.022
(insects chirping)

17:10.069 --> 17:11.570
(device rings)

17:11.570 --> 17:14.742
All right, we need          
        to stay quiet.

17:17.242 --> 17:18.954
- What are you doing?

17:18.954 --> 17:22.249
Are you playing it a         
       lullaby? (chuckles)

17:25.627 --> 17:27.127
(creature roaring)

17:27.127 --> 17:28.297
- Shh, listen.

17:36.430 --> 17:38.974
(distant roaring)

17:38.974 --> 17:42.269
That's her. (chuckles)

17:44.605 --> 17:49.610
- Kind of sounds like a,         
   like a hillbilly mating call.

17:50.402 --> 17:52.654
(Josh chuckles)

17:52.654 --> 17:54.448
- Turn the camera off.

17:54.448 --> 17:55.616
- Wait, I thought            
       you wanted me to...

17:55.616 --> 17:56.825
Dude, what are you doing?

17:56.825 --> 17:57.826
Give me the fucking--        
       - Shh!

17:57.826 --> 17:58.911
Why did you come here?

18:00.162 --> 18:01.580
- Man, my boss sent me here.

18:02.790 --> 18:03.624
- To do what?

18:05.334 --> 18:06.960
- To take you up on your offer.

18:06.960 --> 18:08.921
- Then take me up           
        on my offer, man.

18:10.589 --> 18:12.508
All right, you're a journalist,   
 not a goddamn comedian.

18:20.140 --> 18:22.601
All right, you do it.

18:24.436 --> 18:27.356
I want you to show the world     
   that I ain't playing tricks.

18:28.816 --> 18:29.650
Right?

18:31.110 --> 18:33.612
(tense music)

18:39.993 --> 18:42.371
(rocks clap)

18:49.837 --> 18:51.672
(distant clapping)

18:51.672 --> 18:53.173
She's this way here, come on.

18:53.173 --> 18:55.509
Let's go, let's go, come on.

18:56.510 --> 19:00.681
(tense music continues)

19:00.681 --> 19:03.684
(footsteps thudding)

19:05.978 --> 19:08.063
(sighs) That's her, man.

19:08.063 --> 19:11.358
Look at that, one,            
      two, three, four, five.

19:11.358 --> 19:12.860
You see that?

19:12.860 --> 19:14.403
- That actually             
        kinda looks fresh.

19:14.403 --> 19:16.196
- Hell yeah, it does.

19:17.865 --> 19:19.992
- Someone must have             
    planted it though, right?

19:21.034 --> 19:22.536
- What the heck?

19:22.536 --> 19:24.079
What do you mean             
       someone planted it?

19:24.079 --> 19:25.080
Look at this, there's        
       no way that someone...

19:25.080 --> 19:27.708
(distant roaring)

19:31.003 --> 19:33.338
(tree crashing)

19:33.338 --> 19:34.506
Oh, shit, man.

19:34.506 --> 19:36.175
We gotta go.              
          - What was that?

19:36.175 --> 19:37.718
- Sometimes they fell trees.

19:37.718 --> 19:40.053
It's a scare tactic when      
      they get territorial.

19:40.053 --> 19:41.054
We gotta go now.

19:41.054 --> 19:42.890
- Are we in any danger?

19:42.890 --> 19:44.600
- We're not in danger,          
    but we need to stay quiet,

19:44.600 --> 19:46.435
and we need to get          
        back to camp now.

19:46.435 --> 19:47.436
- [Josh] Okay, let me           
    just finish getting this.

19:47.436 --> 19:48.437
- No, no, come on.

19:48.437 --> 19:49.438
We gotta now, right now.

19:49.438 --> 19:50.063
Come on, let's go.

19:51.440 --> 19:56.028
(distant roaring)            
       (tree trunk crashing)

19:56.904 --> 19:59.364
(footsteps thudding)

20:02.075 --> 20:04.077
- All right, day two.

20:04.077 --> 20:05.913
I checked the trap           
       before Red woke up.

20:05.913 --> 20:08.415
To make sure he              
       didn't mess with it.

20:08.415 --> 20:09.458
It's all still there.

20:10.626 --> 20:11.919
Trip wire was still set.

20:13.962 --> 20:16.757
I leave tomorrow morning,       
    so today's gonna be big.

20:19.301 --> 20:23.138
There was definitely something   
   out there last night,

20:23.138 --> 20:26.934
but someone must have           
    planted the print, right?

20:28.477 --> 20:31.605
- Hey, I'm gonna go          
       shoot some fresh bait.

20:31.605 --> 20:33.106
You all good here?

20:33.106 --> 20:34.775
- Yeah, just working         
       on the video.

20:36.610 --> 20:38.237
- Right?

20:38.237 --> 20:40.155
While I'm gone, can          
       you clean the trap?

20:40.155 --> 20:43.158
- She didn't take           
        any of the bait?

20:43.158 --> 20:45.410
- I think we scared          
       her off last night.

20:45.410 --> 20:48.163
- Hey, about last night, I...

20:48.163 --> 20:51.500
- Quite the show,            
       wasn't it? (laughs)

20:54.127 --> 20:57.089
(foreboding music)

21:00.300 --> 21:02.970
- What's up, big man?        
       - Yo.

21:02.970 --> 21:04.137
- You get some good footage?

21:04.137 --> 21:06.014
- Yep, but he ain't buying it.

21:06.014 --> 21:07.808
- That don't surprise me.       
    - Yeah.

21:08.934 --> 21:10.811
- Well, what you thinking?

21:10.811 --> 21:12.688
- Let's hold off.

21:12.688 --> 21:14.856
No, I'll give you a call if      
   we don't catch anything good

21:14.856 --> 21:16.358
on tape by tonight.

21:16.358 --> 21:17.317
- All right, fair enough.

21:17.317 --> 21:18.819
- Yeah.

21:18.819 --> 21:19.653
- I thought, that ought to work.

21:23.490 --> 21:25.033
- God bless.

21:25.033 --> 21:26.785
Man, I couldn't shoot        
       shit this morning.

21:26.785 --> 21:28.370
- Hey, you always been        
      a shit shot, ain't you?

21:28.370 --> 21:29.496
- [Red] Shut up.

21:29.496 --> 21:31.290
- And on the house.

21:32.708 --> 21:34.835
- Man, I told you I          
       don't do that no more.

21:34.835 --> 21:37.671
- You gonna need the confidence   
 if you gonna be on TV.

21:37.671 --> 21:39.298
- Get rid of it.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.008
God knows you don't          
       need any more of it.

21:41.842 --> 21:42.676
- Fine.

21:43.677 --> 21:45.137
Happy squatching.

21:49.516 --> 21:52.185
(Josh wretches)

21:57.024 --> 21:57.858
Come on.

21:58.900 --> 22:02.029
(mellow guitar music)

22:06.700 --> 22:09.911
(Josh grunts)

22:09.911 --> 22:13.206
(mellow guitar music continues)

22:13.206 --> 22:15.709
(phone rings)

22:17.502 --> 22:20.213
(ringtone rings)

22:22.007 --> 22:24.718
- Hey baby, how's the trip?

22:24.718 --> 22:27.095
- Well, I just cleaned a         
   whole bunch of rotten fruit

22:27.095 --> 22:29.014
from a Bigfoot trap, so.

22:29.014 --> 22:31.058
- [Steph] Say no more.

22:31.058 --> 22:32.893
What's he like?

22:32.893 --> 22:34.353
- You know, I actually          
    think he kind of believes

22:34.353 --> 22:35.520
in all this stuff.

22:37.230 --> 22:38.732
You know, I'm supposed          
    to make this video funny,

22:38.732 --> 22:41.234
but I think I'm              
       starting to feel bad.

22:42.736 --> 22:45.072
- Well, maybe you should      
      change your approach.

22:45.072 --> 22:47.032
- Yeah, but you know,

22:47.032 --> 22:49.910
Tiggs is actually counting      
    on something funny, so.

22:49.910 --> 22:52.746
- Babe, remember            
        it's just a video.

22:52.746 --> 22:53.580
- Right, yeah.

22:55.248 --> 22:59.127
We just, we really           
       need this, you know?

22:59.127 --> 23:02.214
- [Steph] I know, I'm        
       proud of you, really.

23:02.214 --> 23:03.715
- Steph?                 
           - Great story.

23:05.092 --> 23:07.594
Josh?                            
   - Hey, I'm losing you, okay?

23:07.594 --> 23:08.595
- [Steph] Josh?

23:08.595 --> 23:09.471
- I'll be home tomorrow.

23:17.771 --> 23:20.399
(hammer bangs)

23:25.404 --> 23:27.739
That's a lot of meat.

23:27.739 --> 23:29.116
- Ah, yeah, Kyle brought it.

23:29.116 --> 23:30.283
I couldn't kill nothing.

23:31.993 --> 23:33.745
- Shouldn't you put          
       that at the trap?

23:33.745 --> 23:35.122
- I figure we'd leave        
       a trail of breadcrumbs

23:35.122 --> 23:36.623
up to the trap for her.

23:38.291 --> 23:40.168
- Through our campsite?

23:40.168 --> 23:43.296
Isn't that kind of dangerous?

23:43.296 --> 23:45.966
- Well, not if Bigfoot ain't     
   real, it ain't dangerous.

23:48.135 --> 23:49.302
- All right, look, I...

23:50.679 --> 23:52.264
I'm sorry if I've            
       been rude, I just....

23:52.264 --> 23:54.307
- No, hey, look, listen,      
      don't worry about it.

23:54.307 --> 23:55.851
I understand.

23:55.851 --> 23:57.978
You're the journalist         
      and I'm the Bigfoot nut.

23:57.978 --> 23:59.855
